What you need to know:

Rossi made his debut with Juventus in 1973 but the early years of his career were compromised by injury, needing three operations on his kneesAt Perugia, Rossi became embroiled in the 'Totonero' match-fixing scandal and was banned for three years, later reduced to two as he continually protested his innocenceItaly's third World Cup title, and first since the 1930s, owed everything to Rossi, who won the Golden Boot for top-scoring with six goals, the Golden Ball as the tournament's best player, and that year's Ballon d'Or